FrewModel¶

A class used to establish a connection to any Frew model and to manipulate it as required using simple pythonic object oriented syntax.

…

frewpy.frewpy.FrewModel.file_extension¶

The file extension of the Frew model.

Type

str

frewpy.frewpy.FrewModel.file_history¶

Records of when the file has been opened in Frew and by which user.

Type

List[Dict[str, str]]

frewpy.frewpy.FrewModel.file_name¶

The file name of the Frew model including extension.

Type

str

frewpy.frewpy.FrewModel.file_path¶

The absolute file path to the Frew model.

Type

str

frewpy.frewpy.FrewModel.file_version¶

The version of the model file showing the exact build of Frew.

Type

str

frewpy.frewpy.FrewModel.folder_path¶

The absolute folder path to the Frew model, not including the file name.

Type

str

frewpy.frewpy.FrewModel.frew_version¶

The overall Frew version in which the model was created.

Type

str

frewpy.frewpy.FrewModel.json_data¶

The Frew model data loaded in as a Python dictionary.

Type

Dict[str, list]

frewpy.frewpy.FrewModel.num_nodes¶

The number of nodes in the Frew model. This is common across all stages of the Frew model.

Type

int

frewpy.frewpy.FrewModel.num_stages¶

The number of stages in the Frew model.

Type

int

frewpy.frewpy.FrewModel.stage_names¶

The names of all the stages in the Frew model.

Type

List[str]

frewpy.frewpy.FrewModel.titles¶

The project titles including Job Number, Job Title, Sub Title, Calculation Heading, Initials, and Notes.

Type

Dict[str, str]

frewpy.frewpy.FrewModel.get_materials() → List[str]¶

Get names of all the materials used within the Frew model.

frewpy.frewpy.FrewModel.get_material_properties(material: str) → Dict[str, Union[float, int, dict, bool]]¶

Get the properties of a material in the Frew model.

frewpy.frewpy.FrewModel.get_node_levels() → List[float]¶

Get the levels of each node in the Frew model.

frewpy.frewpy.FrewModel.get_results() → Dict[int, dict]¶

Get the shear, bending moment and displacement of the wall for each stage, node and design case.

frewpy.frewpy.FrewModel.results_to_excel() → None¶

Export the wall results to an excel file where each worksheet is a design case. The spreadsheet will be output to the same folder as the models with the suffix ‘_results’.
